						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">On a slab set up close to the temple of Kallēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla I (Jayasimha II)—A.D. 1015.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 937, Rākshasa, Uttarāyaṇa, [Paurṇamāsi]</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">December 24, A.D. 1015.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record certain gifts made by several Gāvuṇḍas of <hi rend="bold">Siḍiyanūru,</hi> when Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara <hi rend="bold">Kali Kāṭimayyarasa</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi-12,000</hi> and his subordinate <hi rend="bold">Vā[vaṇa]rasa</hi> was administering <hi rend="bold">Sattaḷige-70.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
